# Marketing & design — Claude Code skills

This repo’s marketing and design playbooks live in **`.claude/skills/`** (Claude Code format). Jarvis uses them the same way: read the matching `SKILL.md` when the task fits its `description`, then follow it.

## When to load skills

| Trigger | Action |
|--------|--------|
| User says **Jinu** / marketing research | Read `.claude/agents/jinu.md`, `context/brand-context.md`, `context/session-context.md`, then load the relevant skill (e.g. `kol-discovery`, `market-research`, `update-notion`) |
| User says **Nagi** / design work | Read `.claude/agents/nagi.md`, brand context, then load design skills (e.g. `frontend-design`, `figma-craft`, `brand-compliance-review`) |
| Notion writes | Always load `update-notion` first |
| Full research run | Load `run-research` |

## Skill location

```
.claude/skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md
```

Do not wait for slash commands — match task → read skill → execute.

## MCP in Cursor

Skills may reference `mcp__notion__*` / `mcp__chrome__*` (Claude Code names). In Cursor, use the enabled MCP servers from this workspace (Notion, Chrome, Playwright, Figma, Reddit).

## Team bible

Broader rules: root `CLAUDE.md` and `.claude/departments/marketing.md` / `design.md`.
